The course is focused on the literature of Europe from the Middle Ages to the beginning of the 20th century. Throughout the course, comparisons are made with the literatures of Asia and the Middle East, pointing at the connections and global circulation of a variety of literary phenomena - at the process of cultural exchange both among European literatures as well as between the East and the West.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to get acquainted with significant works and literary phenomena of world literature, to acquire a notion of the peculiar genres, literary currents and ideas of those works and to learn to recognize those characteristics in other works of literature. The approach of the course is textual. The specific poetics of an author as well as the characteristics of style and literary current, representing the era, are explained by means of texts through a comparative approach.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student - has read the required amount (at least two thousand pages in two terms) of the works discussed in the course; - analyses the works of literature, noticing their characteristics of literary current, spirituality and style; - realises the global distribution of literary phenomena and produces examples of different types of literary contacts; - explains the concept and content of world literature in different eras; - applies the acquired knowledge of the history of literature to the analysis of other texts; - discusses the works that have been read.
